Let’s make easy 4 ingredient peanut butter fudge!

I’m so excited to be joining Meeghan @caligirlinasouthernworld and Carla @oak.hill.farms today sharing Holiday DIY Ideas! Wait until you see what they’ve shared! You’re going to love it! They have such great ideas! Make sure you follow them and say Hi and let them know I sent you! 

Easy Peanut Butter Fudge
14 oz can sweetened condensed milk 
11 oz bag good quality white chocolate chips. I like Ghirardelli 
1/2 cup peanut butter - either creamy or chunky
1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract 

Line a 8 inch baking dish with parchment paper. I like to spray the dish then add my parchment so the paper sticks. 

Mix all the ingredients in a microwave safe bowl and microwave in 20 second increments, stirring between each burst until blended. Mine takes about 40 seconds. 

Pour mixture in prepared baking dish and spread evenly. Refrigerate for a few hours until firm. 

Cut into pieces and enjoy.

Let’s make Muddy Buddy Snowman Jars!⛄️

It wouldn’t be the holidays with muddy buddies! I make muddy buddies several times during the holiday season! It’s so yummy!

To give this yummy snack as a cute giftie I filled mason jars that I decked out as a snowman. Just add buttons and I tore a piece of homespun for a scarf. 

9 cups rice Chex (you can use corn Chex too)
1/2 cup creamy peanut butter
1 cup milk chocolate chips
4 tablespoons unsalted butter
1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract
Pinch of salt
2 cups powdered sugar
gallon size storage bag
For the jars
Quart size mason jars
buttons
ribbon or torn fabric
hot glue

To make the jars, hot glue buttons on the jar to make the snowman buttons. Set aside
In a large bowl add Chex. Set aside.
In a microwave safe bowl add peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter. Microwave in 30 second increments, stirring between each time until blended and creamy, about 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Pour mixture over Chex and gently mix to coat.
Add 3 cups of Chex into a large gallon size bag along with 2/3 cup powdered sugar and gently shake to coat. Add mixture to a airtight container or jars.
Continue doing this 2 more times with 3 cups of Chex mixture with 2/3 cup powdered sugar.
Store in an airtight container for about 5 days or freeze for up to 3 months. Thaw at room temperature before serving.

Printable recipe on the blog.

Let’s make easy chocolate fudge!

This recipe is a family favorite! I make this several times throughout the holidays because everyone loves it and it’s so easy to make!

Easy Chocolate Fudge
32 oz. bag powdered sugar
1 cup unsweetened cocoa powder
1 cup (2 sticks) unsalted butter, cubed
1/2 cup whole milk
2 tablespoons pure vanilla extract
Optional - Chopped walnut, chopped pretzels, or sprinkles

Line a 9x13 baking dish with parchment paper.
In a large microwave safe bowl mix powdered sugar and cocoa.
Top with cubed butter and milk. Don’t mix.
Microwave for 3 minutes. Stir then microwave in 30 second increments stirring in between each time until blended and creamy. Should be about another minute longer.
Stir in vanilla and optional chopped walnuts or chopped pretzels if desired.
Pour mixture into prepared baking dish and spread evenly.
Top with sprinkles if desired.
Refrigerate until set, at least 1 hour.
Cut into pieces.
Store in an airtight container for up 2 weeks or freeze for up to 3 months.

Let’s make the best Buffalo Chicken Dip!

If you love buffalo chicken you’re going to love this dip! It’s my favorite! I eat with just a spoon!

Not only am I from Buffalo, a huge Buffalo Bills fan (Go Bills!), but I love, love, love all things Buffalo Chicken Dip! It’s my favorite, and my families too!

This Buffalo Chicken Dip takes only a few minutes to make and can even be prepped ahead!

2 10oz cans canned chicken breast, drained and chunks broken up. *canned chicken is the way to go in this recipe!
1/2 cup Buffalo Wing Sauce - I recommend Anchor Bar mild wing sauce 
1 package (8 oz)cream cheese, cubed 
1 cup mayonnaise 
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 
1/2 teaspoon onion powder 
Dash of dried dill
Pinch of salt 

Heat chicken and wing sauce in a large saucepan over medium heat. 

Add remaining ingredients and stir until creamy and cream cheese is melted and not lumpy. 

Pour in serving bowl or keep warm in slow cooker. 

Serve with tortilla chips, celery, carrots or dive in with just a spoon!

Let’s make Jalapeño Popper Pinwheels!

These tasty pinwheels make a easy and yummy game day appetizer, or eve lunch! 

Wait until you try the filling! It’s so good! 

Printable recipe on the blog or save the recipe here!

2 packages (8 oz each) cream cheese (softened)
1 cup shredded cheddar cheese
1/3 cup jarred jalapeno slices, diced
1/4 cup crumbled bacon
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
pinch of salt and pepper
4–5 8-inch flour tortillas

Add all ingredients except tortillas to a large bowl.
Using an electric mixer beat on low until creamy. Season with salt and pepper.
Divide mixture between tortillas and spread evenly.
Tightly roll tortillas and wrap in plastic wrap. Place in the refrigerator for a few hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, cut off ends and cut into slices.

Let’s make Crock Pot Easter Peanut Clusters!

Printable recipe on my blog!

34.5 ounce container of dry roasted peanuts
48 ounce almond bark (I use 2 24 oz. packages from Walmart)
11.4 ounce bag of M&M’s
Sprinkles

Spray Crock Pot with cooking spray and add in peanuts. I do recommend using slow cooker liners for easy clean up.
Chop up almond bark and place on top of peanuts.
Cover and cook on low for 1-1 1/2 hours stirring every 15 minutes until chocolate is melted and mixture is creamy. If your Crock Pot gets a lot of condensation, I do recommend adding a kitchen towel on top before placing the lid so the chocolate doesn’t seize.
Meanwhile line a few large baking sheets with parchment paper.
Turn off heat and reserve 1/2 cup of M&M’s.
Stir in the remaining M&M’s into mixture.
Scoop mixture on to prepared parchment lined baking sheets.
Before chocolate hardens add a few more M&M’s and top with sprinkles. Set aside until clusters harden.
Store in an airtight container.

Winner winner brown sugar Italian chicken dinner!

This 3 ingredient brown sugar Italian chicken is perfect for busy weeknights. I love the prep it ahead too so I can just pop it in the oven when I’m ready to make dinner!

Printable recipe on the blog!

4 (6-7 oz each) boneless, skinless chicken breasts
1/2 cup light brown sugar
1 packet Good Seasons Italian dressing – dry mix only

Line a 9×13 baking dish with aluminum foil and spray with cooking spray.
Place chicken breast in between two pieces of wax paper and lightly pound chicken with a mallet until thickness of chicken breast is even for even cooking.
In a shallow dish mix together brown sugar and the dry Good Seasons Italian dressing mix.
Dip both sides of chicken breast in brown sugar mixture and place in prepared baking dish.
Once all the chicken is covered, sprinkle remaining brown sugar mixture on top.
Cover baking dish and refrigerate until ready to bake.
This can be made the night before or in the morning. This doesn’t need to be prepped ahead if you don’t want to.
TO MAKE

Preheat oven 425 degrees Fahrenheit.
Bake chicken uncovered for 20-25 minutes until chicken is cooked thoroughly and internal temperature of chicken is 165 degrees.
Optional – Remove chicken, increase oven temp to broil then pop chicken under the broiler for a couple of minutes to caramelize the chicken.
Let chicken rest for 5-7 minutes.
TO SERVE

Season chicken with salt and pepper and drizzle brown sugar mixture on top of chicken.

Let’s make easy Swedish Meatballs!

With just 5 ingredients plus salt and pepper you can whip up these delicious Swedish Meatballs perfect for a busy weeknight!

You can even make these in the slow cooker too!

Full recipe on the blog!

20–25 good quality standard-size frozen meatballs (I like the Wegmans frozen meatballs)
1 cup beef broth
1 can (10 oz) cream of mushroom soup
1/4 cup sour cream
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
Salt and pepper to taste
Fresh or dry chopped parsley for serving, optional
Mashed potatoes (I love using store bought mashed potatoes like Bob Evans) or egg noodles for serving.

Defrost meatballs in the microwave for 4-5 minutes until they are not almost thawed through.
Add a little olive oil to a large skillet and add meatballs over medium heat until warmed through.
Stir in beef broth, cream of mushroom soup and sour cream and stir until combined and sauce is heated through.
Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to a simmer and let meatballs simmer in the sauce for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Serve with mashed potatoes or egg noodles.

Let’s make English Muffin Breakfast Casserole. 

This easy and delicious casserole is the perfect dish for brunch of potluck. 

1 6-count package English muffins, cubed
14 oz package ham steak, cubed (or about 1 1/2 cups cubed ham)
2 cups shredded cheddar cheese
1/2 cup diced onion, optional
8 large eggs
2 cups whole milk
Salt 
Pepper 
Garlic powder, optional 

Preheat oven to 350. 

Spray a 9x13 baking dish with cooking spray. 

Add cubed english muffins, cubed ham and 1/2 the cheese to baking dish. 

Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder. 

Mix eggs and milk together. Season with salt and pepper. 

Pour mixture of English muffins. 

Sprinkle top with remaining cheese. 

Cover with foil and bake for 40–45 minutes. 

Remove foil and bake for 10-15 longer. 

Cool for 10-15 minutes. 

*you can swap ham for crumbled cooked sausage

Let’s make the best old-fashioned Iced Oatmeal Cookies!

These have been one of my most popular recipes on my blog for years!

2 cups old-fashioned rolled oats
2 cups all purpose flour
1 tablespoon baking powder
1/2 teaspoon baking soda
1/2 teaspoon salt
2 teaspoons cinnamon
1/2 teaspoon ground nutmeg
1 cup 2 sticks butter, softened
1 cup light brown sugar
1/2 cup sugar
2 large eggs
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
2 cups confectioners sugar
3 tablespoons milk

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray baking sheets with cooking spray and set aside.
Place rolled oats in a food processor and pulse for about 10 seconds until coarse.
Mix oats with flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Using an electric mixer cream butter and sugars.
Add in eggs one at a time then vanilla extract.
Gradually add in flour mixture until combined.
Roll dough into 2 tablespoon size balls and place on baking sheet spacing about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 10-12 minutes until the bottoms begin to brown.
Cool on the baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.
glaze
Mix confectioners sugar and milk together in a medium bowl.
Quickly dip tops of cookies into glaze and let excess drip off.
Place back on wire rack until glaze sets.
Store cookies in an airtight container.

Let’s make easy chocolate fudge!

This recipe is a family favorite! I make this several times throughout the holidays because everyone loves it and it’s so easy to make!

Comment FUDGE and I’ll send you the recipe!

Easy Chocolate Fudge
32 oz. bag powdered sugar
1 cup unsweetened cocoa powder
1 cup (2 sticks) unsalted butter, cubed
1/2 cup whole milk
2 tablespoons pure vanilla extract
Optional - Chopped walnut, chopped pretzels, or sprinkles

Line a 9x13 baking dish with parchment paper.
In a large microwave safe bowl mix powdered sugar and cocoa.
Top with cubed butter and milk. Don’t mix.
Microwave for 3 minutes. Stir then microwave in 30 second increments stirring in between each time until blended and creamy. Should be about another minute longer.
Stir in vanilla and optional chopped walnuts or chopped pretzels if desired.
Pour mixture into prepared baking dish and spread evenly.
Top with sprinkles if desired.
Refrigerate until set, at least 1 hour.
Cut into pieces.
Store in an airtight container for up 2 weeks or freeze for up to 3 months.

Here’s what you need -
1 container refrigerated pizza dough 
Mozzarella cheese sticks cut into 28 1/2-inch pieces 
3 tablespoons butter, melted 
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 
1/2 teaspoon parsley flakes 

Grated Parmesan cheese for garnish 
Marinara for dipping 

Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Roll out pizza dough and cut into 28 squares.
Wrap dough around mozzarella and place seam side down on baking sheet. 
Start with a row of 6, then top with 5, then 4, then 3, then 2, then the last on top. 

Bake for 12-18 minutes.

Whisk together melted butter with garlic powder and parsley flakes and brush on top. 

Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. 

Serve with marinara.

Let’s make easy Swedish Meatballs!

With just 5 ingredients plus salt and pepper you can whip up these delicious Swedish Meatballs perfect for a busy weeknight!

You can even make these in the slow cooker too!

Comment RECIPE and I’ll send you the link for the full printable recipe.

20–25 good quality standard-size frozen meatballs (I like the Wegmans frozen meatballs)
1 cup beef broth
1 can (10 oz) cream of mushroom soup
1/4 cup sour cream
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
Salt and pepper to taste
Fresh or dry chopped parsley for serving, optional
Mashed potatoes (I love using store bought mashed potatoes like Bob Evans) or egg noodles for serving.

Defrost meatballs in the microwave for 4-5 minutes until they are not almost thawed through.
Add a little olive oil to a large skillet and add meatballs over medium heat until warmed through.
Stir in beef broth, cream of mushroom soup and sour cream and stir until combined and sauce is heated through.
Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to a simmer and let meatballs simmer in the sauce for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Serve with mashed potatoes or egg noodles.
